<TITLE> Three killed as truck rams another at Sitakunda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 06 (bdnews24.com)  Three people were killed and one was critically injured when a running truck rammed into a stationary truck on Dhaka-Chittagong highway at Bansbaria at Sitakunda early on Sunday. Mohammed Alam, 22, Ramzan Ali, 30, and Mohammed Sohel, 30 died on spot, police said. An 11-year old boy named Al-Amin sustained critical injuries in the accident and was admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital. Amir Faruk, sergeant of Sitakunda highway police, told bdnews24.com, "Three people died on spot when a running Chittagong-bound truck collided with an out of order stationary truck that was being repaired on the highway at Bansbaria. The driver and helpers of the stationary truck died on the spot." Police could not get hold of the killer truck or its driver. Faruk went on to say that legal steps were being taken regarding the accident. 
